- Update docs/agent-factory-status.md to remove the OAuth-env hypothesis and replace it with the actual fix that landed: stale test text. Otherwise future agents will repeat the diagnosis.
- The OAuth providers in Supabase ARE disabled (Google/Discord client_id null). If anyone ever clicks "Continue with Google" on prod, they'll see Supabase's "provider is not enabled" error. Sign-in card line 63-65 already has friendly error handling for this case. Worth flagging to the human if they care about live OAuth working — but it's out of scope for this v2 task.
- The 12 gameplay-spec timeouts mentioned in the handoff doc (Supabase anon-auth rate limit at 4 workers) — those should resolve by playwright workers being dropped to 2 in PR #99. If they're still timing out at 2 workers, the rate limit is tighter than estimated and worth raising on the Supabase side.

